{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Gm93iLVimPDQn3pUhRmquX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     8→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.Templates;\n     9→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.TemplatesLocale;\n    10→\n    11→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n    12→\n    13→import java.util.List;\n    14→\n    15→@Path(\"/\")\n    16→public class VetResource {\n    17→    \n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    TemplatesLocale templates;\n    20→\n    21→    @GET\n    22→    @Path(\"/vets.html\")\n    23→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    24→    public TemplateInstance showResourcesVetPage() {\n    25→        List<Vet> vets = Vet.listAll();\n    26→        System.out.println(vets);\n    27→        return templates.vetList(vets);\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    @GET\n    31→    @Path(\"/vets\")\n    32→    public Vets showResourcesVetList() {\n    33→        Vets vets = new Vets();\n    34→\t\tvets.getVetList().addAll(Vet.listAll());\n    35→\t\treturn vets;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d081c1a9-d8d9-4333-b4ac-461dffa2ff3d","uuid":"9f3326c0-2ff8-442c-a99e-49c23f9cd6a6"}
