{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01834bun87MChbsWaLgdaTHF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic;\n     2→\n     3→import static io.restassured.RestAssured.when;\n     4→import static org.hamcrest.CoreMatchers.is;\n     5→import static org.hamcrest.CoreMatchers.notNullValue;\n     6→import static org.hamcrest.core.IsNull.nullValue;\n     7→import static org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.ErrorExceptionMapper.ERROR_HEADER;\n     8→import io.quarkus.test.common.http.TestHTTPEndpoint;\n     9→import io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest;\n    10→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n    11→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner.OwnersResource;\n    12→\n    13→@QuarkusTest\n    14→@TestHTTPEndpoint(OwnersResource.class)\n    15→public class OwnersResourceTest {\n    16→\n    17→    @Test\n    18→    void findPage() {\n    19→        when().get(\"find\").then()\n    20→                .statusCode(200)\n    21→                .header(ERROR_HEADER, is(nullValue()));\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    @Test\n    25→    void findAll() {\n    26→        when().get(\"?lastName=\").then()\n    27→                .statusCode(200)\n    28→                .header(ERROR_HEADER, is(nullValue()));\n    29→\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    @Test\n    33→    void existingOwner() {\n    34→        when().get(\"1001\").then()\n    35→                .statusCode(200)\n    36→                .header(ERROR_HEADER, is(nullValue()));\n    37→\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    @Test\n    41→    void invalidOwner() {\n    42→        when().get(\"1\").then()\n    43→                .statusCode(200)\n    44→                .header(ERROR_HEADER, is(notNullValue()));\n    45→\n    46→    }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d081c1a9-d8d9-4333-b4ac-461dffa2ff3d","uuid":"67f63320-d92a-4294-aad9-2be56703d803"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DTxUKZYzARCCshQTgzGR84","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic;\n     2→\n     3→import static io.restassured.RestAssured.when;\n     4→import static org.hamcrest.CoreMatchers.is;\n     5→import static org.hamcrest.core.IsNull.nullValue;\n     6→import static org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.ErrorExceptionMapper.ERROR_HEADER;\n     7→import io.quarkus.test.common.http.TestHTTPEndpoint;\n     8→import io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest;\n     9→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n    10→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner.OwnersResource;\n    11→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet.VetResource;\n    12→\n    13→@QuarkusTest\n    14→@TestHTTPEndpoint(VetResource.class)\n    15→public class VetsResourceTest {\n    16→\n    17→    @Test\n    18→    void vertPage() {\n    19→        when().get(\"vets.html\").then()\n    20→                .statusCode(200)\n    21→                .header(ERROR_HEADER, is(nullValue()));\n    22→    }\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d081c1a9-d8d9-4333-b4ac-461dffa2ff3d","uuid":"a175cc40-c617-4bd7-863d-db1f2da2006a"}
